        "slug": "bookmark-managers-with-cloud-sync",
        "excerpt": "Cloud sync is the difference between bookmarks that work and bookmarks that frustrate. Here are the tools that get sync right.",
        "content": "\n# Bookmark Managers with Cloud Sync\n\nI lost my laptop last year. Everything on it? Gone.\n\nBut my bookmarks? All 600 of them, perfectly intact. Logged into [Markify](https://markify.tech) on my new machine and everything was there. Cloud sync saved me.\n\n## Why Cloud Sync Is Non-Negotiable\n\n**Device death.** Laptops die, phones get lost. Without cloud sync, your bookmarks die with them.\n\n**Multi-device life.** Save at work, find at home, read on the train. That's the promise of cloud sync.\n\n**Collaboration.** Shared collections need a central cloud to sync across team members.\n\n## The Best Cloud Sync Tools\n\n### Markify\n\nInstant sync across all browsers and devices. Encrypted. Never had a sync conflict.\n\n### Raindrop.io\n\nRock-solid sync with complex organizational structures preserved across devices.\n\n### xBrowserSync\n\nSelf-hostable, encrypted, open source. For privacy maximalists.\n\n## Cloud Sync vs. Browser Sync\n\nBrowser sync only works within the same browser. Chrome syncs Chrome bookmarks to Chrome on other devices. That's it.\n\nCloud sync from a dedicated tool works across every browser and platform.\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n### Is cloud sync safe?\nYes, with reputable tools. [Markify](https://markify.tech) encrypts data in transit and at rest.\n\n### What if the cloud service goes offline?\nGood tools cache locally. You can access bookmarks offline.\n\n### Does cloud sync cost money?\nMost tools include sync in their free tier.\n    ",
